Class MQTransformer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.mq.MQTransformer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFromMessageTransformer, IMessageTransformer, IToMessageTransformer, IMessageProcessorEventTransformer

    public class MQTransformer
extends Object
implements IMessageTransformer, IMessageProcessorEventTransformer
    Standard ITransformer for converting between Catalys messages and our default MQSeries data format.

      • toMessage

        public IFIXMessage toMessage(Object source,
                             IFIXMessage target,
                             boolean dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData)
                      throws IllegalArgumentException
        Converts the character based format contained in the given data to an IFIXMessage.
        See documentation (Adapter_IBM_MQ.html) for details of the character format.
        Specified by:
        toMessage in interface IToMessageTransformer
        Parameters:
        source - The data we want to transform to a FIX message. String and byte[] objects are supported.
        target - The message into which the object is to be transformed. Cannot be null.
        dialectAllowNoLengthOnRawData - Ignored.
        Returns:
        IFIXMessage target message (transformed from source)
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - Occurs if there was an error reading 'source'. Given that we are just only expecting character data this should not happen or if there is insufficient data in the buffer (as indicated by the length fields contained in the message - see Adapter_IBM_MQ.html)
        NullPointerException - if target was null
